            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> So, for the issue witch needs:vim-patch label, start a PR in vim first is better?\r\n\r\nmark this PR as draft and create a PR in vim.  \r\n\r\nThe idea is to drop the busy-wait arm a timer for autocompletedelay, return to the insert loop, and show the pum in the timer callback, so the autocmds fire naturally at the top-of-loop `ins_redraw` (no re-entrancy, no blocking).\r\nVim and Neovim differ here though, Vim's loop already waits for input with a timeout, so it can reuse that poll timeout, Neovim is libuv based, so it'd be a `time_watcher/uv_timer` posting back to the loop. Since it's ported from Vim, probably easiest to do it the poll timeout way there first and mirror it here 😮‍💨",
